{"questionId":"12700","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An archaeological site is to be made accessible for viewing by the public. To do this, archaeologists built two straight paths from point A to point B and from point B to point C as shown in the following diagram. The length of path AB is 185 m, the length of path BC is 250 m, and angle <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\\mathop {\\text{B}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{C}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>B</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is 125°.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/b7f4507ebf6c5ecb2ada1183ac19a3092107e83e.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The archaeologists plan to build two more straight paths, AD and DC. For the paths to go around the site, angle <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\\mathop {\\text{A}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{D}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>A</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>D</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is to be made equal to 85° and angle <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\\mathop {\\text{C}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{D}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>C</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>D</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is to be made equal to 70° as shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/4595aacbb4a0b674d6b85168b78a8b870527c126.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the size of&nbsp;angle <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\\mathop {\\text{C}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{D}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>C</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>D</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(ACD = ) 70° − (180° − 125° − 31.9478°…)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for subtracting their angle <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\\mathop {\\text{C}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{B}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>C</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> from 70°.</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>(ADC =) 360 − (85 + 70 + 125) = 80</p>\n<p>(ACD =) 180 − 80 − 53.0521...&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>46.9°&nbsp; (46.9478…°) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)<em>(G2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through from part (b)(i).</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12700","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.T_2c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the size of angle A C ∧ ⁡ D .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Prior learning","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}